HEADWORD: Inarch
<hw>In*arch"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Inarched</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Inarching</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To graft by uniting,
as a scion, to a stock, without separating either from its root before
the union is complete; -- also called to <altname>graft by
approach</altname>.</def> <rj><au>P. Miler.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

